result.execSummary:
All charges against Daniel Joseph Samplaski in this case have been dismissed. These charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Daniel Joseph Samplaski is presumed innocent.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Daniel Joseph Samplaski in court, in custody.  Attorney Erica N Young in court for Daniel Joseph Samplaski.  Attorney Nate McClure in court for State of Wisconsin. State made a record. On motion of the state, Court dismissed the case without prejudice.
Defense counsel contacted the Court requesting an adjournment. Case adjourned off the record. Case remains calendared in Br 13. Parties advised of the new date.
Signed and filed, No Contact Order.  Defendant to have no contact with PO
Court ordered defendant TURNED OVER TO Justice Point for SUPERVISION Level 3. No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Daniel Joseph Samplaski appeared by video, in custody.  Attorney Brett Lee Copeland appeared by video for Daniel Joseph Samplaski.  Attorney Karine O'Byrne appeared by video for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant is advised this case is assigned to Reserve Judge, Branch 13.  Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause.  Defendant advised of right to counsel and complaint given to defendant's attorney.  Defendant pled not guilty.  DEFENDANT IS INDIGENT AND QUALIFIES FOR PUBLIC DEFENDER REPRESENTATION.  Case is adjourned to Branch 13.
Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 26, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
Defendant in Custody, Court appearance today in Intake Court, Room 137A.
